>\r\n                                            <p></p>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <p></p>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                sub-sub-components\r\n                                </td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    Returns the data for the individual sub-subcomponents passed in on the request. Also compares the scores of the returned sub-sub-components and ranks the states accordingly.<p></p>\r\n                                    <p>Sub-subcomponents are passed in as a pipe-delimited list of the sub-subcomponents name.</p>\r\n                                    <h4>Example</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey&amp;sub-sub-subcomponents=reading|math|science</p>\r\n                                    <div class="row">\r\n                                        <div class="large-12 medium-12 columns">\r\n                                            <div class="parameter-link">\r\n                                                <a href="#">Available U.S. Sub-subcomponents \r\n                                                <i class="fi-arrow-down"></i>\r\n                                                <i class="fi-arrow-up"></i></a>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class="parameter-list">\r\n                                                <strong>8th_grade_test_scores:</strong><br>\r\n                                                reading<br>\r\n                                                math<br>\r\n                                                science<br>\r\n                                                <strong>high_school_dropout_rate:</strong><br>\r\n                                                prevalence_of_charter_schools<br>\r\n                                                educational_freedom<br>\r\n                                                <strong>religious_engagement:</strong><br>\r\n                                                importance_of_religion<br>\r\n                                                religious_attendance<br>\r\n                                                <strong>perceived_improvement_in_living_standard:</strong><br>\r\n                                                perceived_improvement_in_personal_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                perceived_improvement_in_personal_financial_situation\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <p></p>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div class="large-12 medium-12 columns">\r\n                                            <div class="parameter-link">\r\n                                                <a href="#">Available World Sub-subcomponents \r\n                                                    <i class="fi-arrow-down"></i><i class="fi-arrow-up"></i>\r\n                                                </a>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <div class="parameter-list">\r\n                                                <strong>communications_infrastructure:</strong><br>\r\n                                                mobile_phone_subscriptions<br>\r\n                                                broadband_internet_subscriptions<br>\r\n                                                <strong>perceived_current_living_standard:</strong><br>\r\n                                                perceived_personal_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                perceived_national_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                <strong>perceived_improvement_in_living_standard:</strong><br>\r\n                                                perceived_improvement_in_personal_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                perceived_improvement_in_national_living_standard<br>\r\n                                                <strong>religious_engagement:</strong><br>\r\n                                                importance_of_religion<br>\r\n                                                religious_attendance<br>\r\n                                                <strong>prevalence_of_marriage:</strong><br>\r\n                                                marriage_rate<br>\r\n                                                self_reported_marriage<br>\r\n                                                <strong>prevalence_of_divorce:</strong><br>\r\n                                                divorce_rate<br>\r\n                                                self_reported_divorce\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                            <p></p>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <p></p>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                        </tbody>\r\n                    </table>\r\n                    <p>These Parameters can be combined to increase the specificity of your search. For example:</p>\r\n                    <p>http://life-measures.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey&amp;locations=va|md|pa&amp;years=2002|2003|2004&amp;dimensions=opportunity|health_and_environment|freedom</p>\r\n                    <p>or</p>\r\n                    <p>http://life-measures.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/int/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey&amp;locations=af|al|dz&amp;years=2002|2003|2004&amp;dimensions=opportunity|health_and_environment|freedom</p>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n    </div>', 'Quality of Life', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-03-03 17:35:50', '2015-03-03 17:35:50', '', 4, 'http://localhost/life-measures-wordpress/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
	(104, 1, '2015-03-03 17:38:58', '2015-03-03 17:38:58', '<section class="intro-image" style="background-image: url(\'http://www.staging-putty.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/cki-template11-headers-api.jpg\');">\r\n        <header>\r\n                            <h1>How to Use Our Data API</h1>\r\n                <hr/>\r\n                    </header>\r\n    </section>\r\n\r\n<div class="row">\r\n\r\n            <section class="post standard">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2>Introduction</h2>\r\n                    <hr/>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <p>Before you can access the API data, you will first need to get a registration key that you will need to use on all of your requests. <a href="/get-the-data/api-registration/">Click here</a> to get your registration key.</p>\r\n<p>To gain access to raw information regarding the locations, dimensions, components, and scores affiliated with each Index (U.S. Index or World Index), please use one of the following URL use cases.</p>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n            <section class="post standard">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2>Resources</h2>\r\n                    <hr/>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>\r\n            Resources\r\n        </th>\r\n<th>\r\n            Description\r\n        </th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/locations/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/locations/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<strong>Locations</strong><br />\r\n            Returns a list of all states or nations included in the Well-Being Initiative’s Index.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/dimensionlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/dimensionlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<strong>Dimensions</strong><br />\r\n            Returns a list of the dimensions of well-being, which are shared by the U.S. and World Indices.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/componentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/componentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><strong>Components</strong><br />\r\n            Returns a list of all components (and their parent dimensions) included in the U.S. and World Indices.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/subcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/subcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><strong>Sub-Components</strong><br />\r\n            Returns a list of all sub-components (and their parent components) included in the U.S. and World Indices.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/subsubcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/subsubcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><strong>Sub-Sub-Components</strong><br />\r\n            Returns a list of all sub-sub-components (and their parent sub-components) included in the U.S. and World Indices.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n            <section class="post standard">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2>Scores</h2>\r\n                    <hr/>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<th>Scores</th>\r\n<th>Description</th>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/summary/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/summary/?key=yourRegistrationKey</td>\r\n<td><strong>Summary Scores</strong><br />\r\nReturns all states or nations, scores and rankings related with the Well-Being Initiative’s Index for the most recent year that we have data.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</td>\r\n<td><strong>All Scores</strong><br />\r\nReturns all states or nations, dimensions, components, subcomponents, sub-sub-components, scores and rankings related with the Well-Being Initiative’s Index. Includes historical data back to 2001 for US data, and 2000 for World data.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/dimensions/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/dimensions/?key=yourRegistrationKey</td>\r\n<td><strong>Dimension Scores</strong><br />\r\nReturns all dimension scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Index.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/components/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/components/?key=yourRegistrationKey</td>\r\n<td><strong>Component Scores</strong>Returns all component scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Index.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/subcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/subcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</td>\r\n<td><strong>Sub-Component Scores</strong><br />\r\nReturns all sub-component scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Index.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/subsubcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<h4>World</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/subsubcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</td>\r\n<td><strong>Sub-Sub-Component Scores</strong><br />\r\nReturns all sub-sub-component scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Index.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n            <section class="post standard">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2>Targeted Queries</h2>\r\n                    <hr/>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <p>Generating targeted lists of specific data points is done by adding query parameters to your URL. This can allow you to specify your search criteria (ex.; locations, years, dimensions, components, etc.) and get a detailed object of that data as well as a calculated score and ranking based on the returned data.</p>\r\n<h3>Base URLs</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n            U.S.\r\n        </td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<p>            This call will return all states, dimensions, components, subcomponents, sub-sub-components, and all of the scores related to the Well-Being Initiative’s U.S. Index. Includes historical data back to 2001.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n            World\r\n        </td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/int/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n<p>            This call will return all countries, dimensions, components, subcomponents, sub-sub-components, and all of the scores related to the Well-Being Initiative’s World Index. Includes historical data back to 2000.\r\n        </td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>Parameters</h3>\r\n<table>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n            locations\r\n        </td>\r\n<td>\r\n            Returns all of the data for the individual states passed in on the request. Also compares the scores of the returned states and ranks them accordingly.</p>\r\n<p>            States and countries are passed in as a pipe-delimited list of the two-letter state/country abbreviations.</p>\r\n<h4>Example</h4>\r\n<p>http://www.staging-putty.org/api/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey&#038;locations=ca|ny|va</p>\r\n<div class="row">\r\n<div class="large-6 medium-6 columns">\r\n<div class="parameter-link"><a href="#">Available U.S. Locations <i class="fi-arrow-down"></i><i class="fi-arrow-up"></i></a></div>\r\n<div class="parameter-list">\r\n                        AL &rarr; Alabama<br />\r\n                        AK &rarr; Alaska<br />\r\n                        AZ &rarr; Arizona<br />\r\n                        AR &rarr; Arkansas<br />\r\n                        CA &rarr; California<br />\r\n                        CO &rarr; Colorado<br />\r\n                        CT &rarr; Connecticut<br />\r\n                        DE &rarr; Delaware<br />\r\n                        FL &rarr; Florida<br />\r\n                        GA &rarr; Georgia<br />\r\n                        HI &rarr; Hawaii<br />\r\n                        ID &rarr; Idaho<br />\r\n                        IL &rarr; Illinois<br />\r\n                        IN &rarr; Indiana<br />\r\n                        IA &rarr; Iowa<br />\r\n                        KS &rarr; Kansas<br />\r\n                        KY &rarr; Kentucky<br />\r\n                        LA &rarr; Louisiana<br />\r\n                        ME &rarr; Maine<br />\r\n                        MD &rarr; Maryland<br />\r\n                        MA &rarr; Massachusetts<br />\r\n                        MI &rarr; Michigan<br />\r\n                        MN &rarr; Minnesota<br />\r\n                        MS &rarr; Mississippi<br />\r\n                        MO &rarr; Missouri<br />\r\n                        MT &rarr; Montana<br />\r\n                        NE &rarr; Nebraska<br />\r\n                        NV &rarr; Nevada<br />\r\n                        NH &rarr; New Hampshire<br />\r\n                        NJ &rarr; New Jersey<br />\r\n                        NM &rarr; New Mexico<br />\r\n                        NY &rarr; New York<br />\r\n                        NC &rarr; North Carolina<br />\r\n                        ND &rarr; North Dakota<br />\r\n                        OH &rarr; Ohio<br />\r\n                        OK &rarr; Oklahoma<br />\r\n                        OR &rarr; Oregon<br />\r\n                        PA &rarr; Pennsylvania<br />\r\n                        RI &rarr; Rhode Island<br />\r\n                        SC &rarr; South Carolina<br />\r\n                        SD &rarr; South Dakota<br />\r\n                        TN &rarr; Tennessee<br />\r\n                        TX &rarr; Texas<br />\r\n                        UT &rarr; Utah<br />\r\n                        VT &rarr; Vermont<br />\r\n                        VA &rarr; Virginia<br />\r\n                        WA &rarr; Washington<br />\r\n                        WV &rarr; West Virginia<br />\r\n                        WI &rarr; Wisconsin<br />\r\n                        WY &rarr; Wyoming\r\n                    </div>\r\n</p></div>\r\n<div class="large-6 mediu